result.execSummary:
The defendant Luis A. Luna was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st Degree Child Sex Assault - Sexual Contact with Person under Age of 13, a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(1)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Pay court costs and Department of Corrections Supervision Fees.  If the defendant is discharged from Extended Supervision with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.

Follow through with all treatment recommendations (i.e. sex offender, anger management), as deemed ncecessary by the Agent.
-------------------------

-------------------------

Comply with the State of Wisconsin Sex Offender Registry.   Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.
-------------------------

11:13 am  Court in session.  Case called.  Appearances given.  Haley Jo Johnson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Luis A. Luna in court, in custody with attorney Francis P Raff.  Interpreter Sarah Tapia is sworn by Clerk.  
Court recites charges and maximum potential penalties.  Court notes that files were dismissed and read-in.  Matter is before the Court for sentencing.  
Court will first proceed with the change of plea in file 2016CM511.  Atty Raff files Plea Questionnaire.  Atty Johnson makes record with regard to victim notification.  Atty Raff makes record as to the plea agreement on each of the files.  -------------
Court has plea colloquy with Mr. Luna as to charge in file 2016CM511.  
Deft pleads GUILTY to Ct 1 in file 2016CM511.  
Court finds Deft's plead has been made freely knowingly and intelligently and he is voluntarily choosing to waive his constitution rights and plead guilty - accepts plea - finds guilty
11:24 am  Court proceeds to sentencing on files.  Court would like to know the reasons for the joint recommendation of the parties in light of the agreement set forth in the PSI.  
11:24 am  Argument by Atty Johnson in support of the proposed plea agreement.  
11:26 am  Court goes over corrections that need to be made to the PSI.  Court references page 5 which indicates that both of defendant's prior files were expunged.  Court makes record as to what happened to the 2012 files.  Atty Johnson makes further record as to reasons for the agreement that was reached.  
11:31 am  Atty Raff makes record in support of plea agreement.  Atty Raff did not have any additional corrections to the PSI other than those cited by the Court.  11:38 am  Statement by Mr. Luna-Chavez.  
11:39 am  Court proceeds with making its record and sentencing the defendant.  Court has reviewed the file as well as the PSI.  Court will adopt the joint recommendation being made by the parties.  

SENTENCE - File 2016CF000034:  
Eighteen (18) yrs Prison; 8 yrs IC followed by 10 yrs ES;  
353 days of sentence credit;  NOT eligible for CIP or SAP;  

CONDITIIONS OF ES:  
1)  No contact with anyone under the age of 18, other than incidental, without Agent approval.  
2)  Follow through with all treatment recommendations (i.e., sex offender, anger management) as deemed necessary by Agent.  
3)  No contact with the victims or their mother.  
4)  Comply with the State of Wisconsin Sex Offender Registry.  
5)  Pay court costs and DOC supervision fees.  
6)  Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
State filed Motion for HIV / STD Testing and the Defense has no objection.  Court will sign the Order submitted by Atty Johnson.  
Court gives warnings:  1)  May not possess firearms; 2) May not vote until civil rights are restored; 3)  May not possess body armor; 4) May not work / volunteer with children (Sec. 948.13);  
---------
SENTENCE - File 2014CM000087:  
Ninety (90) days in Jail, conc with 2016CF000034;  
90 days of dead time credit;  Pay court costs;  
---------
SENTENCE - File 2016CM000511:  
$100.00 fine plus court costs;  
11:50 am  Court in recess.
Vicki Bermudez
